TESDA TRAINERS METHODOLOGY - D4

UTILIZE IT APPLICATIONS IN TECHNICAL TRAINING
-Utilizing IT applications means the trainer uses digital tools and technology to enhance teaching, learning, and assessment.
-These tools help make training more interactive, efficient, and accesible, especially in competency-based training.
Examples
  -Classroom Presentation
    >The trainer uses MSPPT to present lessons with visual, videos, and animations.
  -Online Communication
    >The trainer uses Google Classroom or Messenger to send announcements, assignments, and updates
  -Virtual TRaining Sessiions
    >The trainer conducts online classes such as Zoom
  -Technical Skills Training (CSS Example)
    >The trainer uses computer appliations to demonstrate software installation or troubleshooting
  -Digital Assessment
    >The trainer creates quizes using Google Forms for quick evaluation of learner understanding.

Benefits
  -Enhances learning experience and participation
  -Saves time and effort in managing training
  -Provides real-world digital skills
  -Supports flexible and remote training


LEAD SMALL TEAMS
-it focuses on the trainer's ability to guide, organize, and motivate a group in order to achieve common goals effecively and harmonously.
-A trainer who can lead small teams helps learners develop teamwork, communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills that are essential in the workplace.

Key responsibilities:
-Set clear goals and directions
-Assign roles and responsibilities
-Encourage teamwork and participation
-Monitor and support team performance
-Resolve conflicts and maintain positive relationships
-Evaluate performance and provide feedback

Benefits
-Builds cooperation and trust
-Improves communication skills
-Enhances learning through collaboration
-Prepares learners for real workplace situations

